						               													<description>One of twelve Money Target Amount Cards is drawn at random. These cards range in amount from &amp;pound;49,000 to &amp;pound;80,000. When playing multiplayer, the player to reach this target amount in ten turns or fewer is the winner. When playing solitaire, reaching this target amount in ten turns is a victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are twenty Colour Money Cards  which represent the twenty cash machines from the British television game show. Each card represents a different payout ranging from &amp;pound;1,000 to &amp;pound;20,000 in &amp;pound;1,000 increments.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A turn begins by choosing a Colour Money Card and logging in the card&amp;rsquo;s number into the electronic Money Module. Every player puts one hand on the Money Module. It begins to count up from &amp;pound;1,000 in &amp;pound;1,000 increments. Any player who stops the module before it reaches its payout limit adds the amount when the device was stopped to one&amp;rsquo;s own score. Any player who waits too long receives nothing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Even though the television series has one player playing against the house, this is a faithful adaption of the series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
